data.name: DatabaseRange
desc: represents a database range in a spreadsheet document.
A database range is a name for a cell range that also stores filtering, sorting, subtotal and data import settings and options.

properties.name: AutoFilter
desc: specifies whether the AutoFilter is enabled or not.

properties.name: ContainsHeader
desc: specifies whether this range includes a top row of headers.

properties.name: FilterCriteriaSource
desc: specifies the range where the filter can find the filter criteria.
This is only used if SheetFilterDescriptor.UseFilterCriteriaSource is TRUE.

properties.name: FromSelection
desc: specifies whether the imported data is only a selection of the database.

properties.name: KeepFormats
desc: if this property is set, cell formats are extended when the size of the range is changed by an update operation.

properties.name: MoveCells
desc: if this property is set, columns or rows are inserted or deleted when the size of the range is changed by an update operation.

properties.name: RefreshPeriod
desc: specifies the time between two refresh actions in seconds.

properties.name: StripData
desc: if this property is set, the cell contents within the database range are left out when the document is saved.

properties.name: TokenIndex
desc: returns the index used to refer to this range in token arrays.
A token describing a database range shall contain the op-code obtained from the FormulaMapGroupSpecialOffset.DB_AREA and this index as data part.

properties.name: TotalsRow
desc: specifies whether this range includes a bottom row of totals.

properties.name: UseFilterCriteriaSource
desc: specifies whether the filter criteria should be taken from a CellRange.
